  "tips": [
    "Don’t Overmix: A few lumps in the batter are totally fine—overmixing makes pancakes tough, not fluffy.",
    "Rest the Batter: Letting the batter sit for 10 minutes helps the baking powder activate and the gluten relax, resulting in lighter pancakes.",
    "Even Heat: Medium-low heat is key. Too hot and they’ll burn outside before cooking through.",
    "Perfect Flipping: Wait for bubbles and set edges before flipping—patience is everything!"
